author: CARBINEZzZz
text:
I remember watching this when it happened, and it was actually at that exact moment that I gave up on ever playing CS:GO professionally. I already had felt like a lot of the people I matched against online were hacking just based on how ridiculously accurate some of them were and how some people just had insane amounts of kills at the end of the game compared to everyone else, even the people on their team.

Some of this was in fact smurfing and not hacking, which isn't much better tbh, but either way I realized that there was literally no point in trying to go pro at this game unless I wanted to start diving into some shady business, which I don't.

Who knows, maybe I was just bad at the game. It's still no fun to play a game where every time you get killed in some ridiculous way or experience a match blowout you really can't help but wonder if the other team is legit, and your concerns may very well be justified based on the statistical number of hackers in this game.

author: Ali Khan
text:
I also blame the administrators/organizers at local level who let cheaters like this go through. I dont know how it is now but back in 2004 I was competing in WCG and I got into the regional finals for FIfa 2004. The winner would then compete for a India level finals in Mumbai and the final winner would go on to represent India in WCG finals in California. So I was in the finals and I was 20 at that time and I was playing a 12 year old kid who had his father watching him behind his back. Firstly the WCG rules clearly stated that you could only use National teams and not clubs and clubs were much stronger in the game. The kid was playing with the best club team in the game and I protested that it is against the rules but nobody gave a fuck. I had practiced using a National team for months and had to go along with it but the kid already had an advantage. First game we start playing and I score first, but as soon as I scored the game disconnected. We were told to restart and I told them that I should start with a 1-0 lead but no body gave a fuck. Anyway second game, same thing happens, I score first and game disconnects as soon as I score. We were again asked to start from beginning and I didnt get to start from 1-0. I was already pissed and not able to keep my cool so third game stayed 0-0 close to the end and then he scored. After that he started wasting time which was also against the rules but again no body gave a fuck. He went on to win it and then I realized what happened. The kid was exploiting a glitch in the game where he started hitting the shift key every time I scored which would activate sticky keys and disconnect the game. I brought that to the attention of the organizers and guess what, NOBODY GAVE A FUCK.

SO that kid went on to play the finals in Mumbai and imagine if he made it through using same tactics and went on to represent India internationally
